author: dark_mouse
text: I am just laughing see all those people saying Rain is nothing but ordinary. Do you know how difficult it was to promote worldwide in 2004 without the use of social media? There was no smart device, only limited internet and computers were not that handy (at least for me I accessed them at school). Nowadays one group posts a video on YouTube the next day fans around the globe could readily react to it. Rain’s advancement to Hollywood, or at least to South East Asia, were very amazing those days. I live in Hong Kong and even my mom who aged 7x knew who Rain was back then in 2004. He might not be a “world star” to your standard, but he was definitely a household name. Please don’t understate his or JYP’s influence. Last but not least, Rain and idols such as Lee Hyori, GOD and many others, unlike some idols from more affluent background nowadays, worked their ass off back then from very poor family background to where they are today. At least their hard work deserve your respect.
